issue_comments.body:
@tliron You might want to reconsider your setup. You said you're running Ubuntu GNOME with DockX. Instead of doing that, you could simply run KDE Plasma 5 (i.e. Kubuntu or even better KDE neon).

You can actually configure the task manager in the Plasma 5 panel to work like DockbarX/DockX. Plasma 5 has this functionality built-in, no need to add anything. And it even has window thumbnail previews.

Just saying, since DockbarX does no longer seem to be actively maintained and Plasma 5 works really well in that regard.

@anggerbagus, thanks this worked, ~~but I think perhaps it's revealed an unsupported feature.  I can't figure out if it's possible to show windows that only exist on the same monitor as the respective dock.  Any idea?~~

